metadata.name: Abstract Life #21
metadata.description:
The concept of organic, obtained from living systems, is said to be an effect that, like a plant and a living being, has grown in a completely dynamic manner in different degrees, and no factor except vital forces has prevented its growth. Organic creation is an example of this type. L√©onard de Vinci believed in nature; he wrote, "Painting is a child of nature" in his opinion, art should be compatible with nature. His public image of creativity was "innovation while maintaining fidelity" to nature. According to Michelangelo, the form the artist gives to the materials is in the artist's mind and the materials themselves. Therefore, the artist is always in a metaphysical struggle with the form and secrets of nature. This is a revelatory process through which the artist discovers the mass of paper already hidden in his mind and the materials. As an architect, I tried to create this work while paying attention to the structuralism of shapes and forms in creation, inspired by the colors in nature and my experience in painting and illustration.

To spread the vibe of my beautiful community, minters will own 50% of royalty on each secondary sale.
Eighteen different color palettes and three different borders are used in this artwork.
Made in p5js
Created August 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi

metadata.name: Ocean #91
metadata.description:
Ocean is my second long-form generative work continuing my exploration of creating visual designs with polygons. As found with the name, Ocean, this piece is inspired by patterns of ocean waves, storms, typhoons, and urchins. Ocean is composed of six layout variations and four color palettes with a few singular inspirations.

Click on the image to save 1400x1400 png

metadata.name: R3B00T #31
metadata.description:
The variety of noises is infinite. If today, when we have perhaps a thousand different machines, we can distinguish a thousand different noises, 
tomorrow, as new machines multiply, we will be able to distinguish ten, twenty, or thirty thousand different noises, 
not merely in a simply imitative way, but to combine them according to our imagination.
- Luigi Russolo (The Art of Noises, 1916)

___

Generative visual, noise algorithm, organic pattern, inspired by compact disc format, transform in autonomous system, and made with code.

* Interactive feature :
- Place your mouse cursor to visual screen (canvas)
- Left click to spin the cd and play audio
- Right click to reset or back to original

* Every piece in this project have different unique audio. (All sounds created with modular synthesizer)
